   \]
   Simplifying, we get \( n \equiv 56 \mod 17 \).
3. Reduce \( 56 \mod 17 \):
   - Since \( 17 \times 3 = 51 \), we have \( 56 - 51 = 5 \).
   - Therefore, \( 56 \equiv 5 \mod 17 \).
4. Conclude that \( n \equiv 5 \mod 17 \).

